# VelaFlow Snyk policy file.
#
# Reviewed quarterly or on any significant refactor to the affected paths.
# After R17.2 every path-traversal and tar-slip finding is fixed at the
# source via src/brain/security/safe_path.py (see module docstring for
# the Snyk CWE-22 sanitizer rationale), per-member tar.extractfile()
# with inline Path.resolve().relative_to(target) sanitizers at each
# write sink, os.fchmod(fd, ...) in place of chmod(path, ...) to avoid
# path-taint sinks on file-mode changes, and pathlib.Path.open()
# append writes in the action ledger. This file retains no active
# ignores — a failing Snyk Code run blocks the build.
version: v1.25.0
ignore: {}
patch: {}
